                            <comment id="34383" author="balex" created="Fri, 4 Apr 2008 19:09:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed to SVN revision  2866.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I clarified in the JavaDocs the desired behavior, and also modified LookupStrategy (and the BasicLookupStrategy implementation) to never throw NotFoundException. However, the AclService methods all throw NotFoundException if an Acl is missing. This therefore permits a chain of LookupStrategy instances to be used, to automatically generate Acl instances at runtime if there was none found in the database.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Tests pass.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
